\f1\b  September 17, 1826.\
\

\f0\b0 \uc0\u55356 \u56812 \u55356 \u56807 
\f1\b On this day Georg Friedrich Bernhard Riemann
\f2\b0  (1826-1866), the famous German {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematics"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 mathematician}}\cf4 , was born.\cf2  He made contributions to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mathematical_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 analysis}}, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Number_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 number theory}}, and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Differential_geometry"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 differential geometry}}. In the field of real analysis, he is mostly known for the first rigorous formulation of the integral, the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_integral"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Riemann integral}}, and his work on {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fourier_series"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Fourier series}}. His contributions to {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Complex_analysis"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 complex analysis}} include most notably the introduction of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_surfaces"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Riemann surfaces}}, breaking new ground in a natural, geometric treatment of complex analysis. His famous {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/On_the_Number_of_Primes_Less_Than_a_Given_Magnitude"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 1859 paper}} on the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime-counting_function"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 prime-counting function}}, containing the original statement of the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemann_hypothesis"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 Riemann hypothesis}}, is regarded as one of the most influential papers in {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytic_number_theory"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 analytic number theory}}. Through his pioneering {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Riemannian_Geometry"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 contributions to differential geometry}}, Riemann laid the foundations of the mathematics of {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/General_relativity"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 general relativity}}. He is considered by many to be one of the greatest mathematicians of all time.
